SIMPLE: survivor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Survivor
<hw>Sur*viv"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
survives or outlives another person, or any time, event, or
thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>survivor</qex> bound⟦br⟧
In filial obligation for some term⟦br⟧
To do obsequious sorrow.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The longer liver of two joint
tenants, or two persons having a joint interest in anything.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Survivorship</ent>⟦br⟧
